column2: writes        The total number of region entries that have been written to disk. A write is done every time an entry is created on disk or every time its value is modified on disk.
column3: writeTime        The total amount of time spent writing to disk
column4: writtenBytes        The total number of bytes that have been written to disk
column5: flushes        The total number of times the an entry has been flushed from the async queue.
column6: flushTime        The total amount of time spent doing an async queue flush.
column7: flushedBytes        The total number of bytes written to disk by async queue flushes.
column8: reads        The total number of region entries that have been read from disk
column9: readTime        The total amount of time spent reading from disk
column10: readBytes        The total number of bytes that have been read from disk
column11: recoveriesInProgress        current number of persistent regions being recovered from disk
column12: recoveryTime        The total amount of time spent doing a recovery
column13: recoveredBytes        The total number of bytes that have been read from disk during a recovery
column14: recoveredEntryCreates        The total number of entry create records processed while recovering oplog data.
column15: recoveredEntryUpdates        The total number of entry update records processed while recovering oplog data.
column16: recoveredEntryDestroys        The total number of entry destroy records processed while recovering oplog data.
column17: recoveredValuesSkippedDueToLRU        The total number of entry values that did not need to be recovered due to the LRU.
column18: recoveryRecordsSkipped        The total number of oplog records skipped during recovery.
column19: oplogRecoveries        The total number of oplogs recovered
column20: oplogRecoveryTime        The total amount of time spent doing an oplog recovery
column21: oplogRecoveredBytes        The total number of bytes that have been read from oplogs during a recovery
column22: removes        The total number of region entries that have been removed from disk
column23: removeTime        The total amount of time spent removing from disk
column24: queueSize        The current number of entries in the async queue waiting to be flushed to disk
column25: compactInserts        Total number of times an oplog compact did a db insert
column26: compactInsertTime        Total amount of time, in nanoseconds, spent doing inserts during a compact
column27: compactUpdates        Total number of times an oplog compact did an update
column28: compactUpdateTime        Total amount of time, in nanoseconds, spent doing updates during a compact
column29: compactDeletes        Total number of times an oplog compact did a delete
column30: compactDeleteTime        Total amount of time, in nanoseconds, spent doing deletes during a compact
column31: compactsInProgress        current number of oplog compacts that are in progress
column32: writesInProgress        current number of oplog writes that are in progress
column33: flushesInProgress        current number of oplog flushes that are in progress
column34: compactTime        Total amount of time, in nanoseconds, spent compacting oplogs
column35: compacts        Total number of completed oplog compacts
column36: openOplogs        Current number of oplogs this disk store has open
column37: compactableOplogs        Current number of oplogs ready to be compacted
column38: inactiveOplogs        Current number of oplogs that are no longer being written but are not ready ready to compact
column39: oplogReads        Total number of oplog reads
column40: oplogSeeks        Total number of oplog seeks
column41: uncreatedRecoveredRegions        The current number of regions that have been recovered but have not yet been created.
column42: backupsInProgress        The current number of backups in progress on this disk store
column43: backupsCompleted        The number of backups of this disk store that have been taking while this VM was alive
